The paper presents a technique for efficient training of deep neural networks using low-confidence labels and simultaneous learning of machines and experts. This technique can be applied to various domains, including brain monitoring at intensive care units, which suggests a connection to the sub-categories of machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), computer vision (cs.CV), and neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE). The paper also mentions the use of a neural embedding function and a memory module, which relates to the sub-category of natural language processing (cs.CL).
